  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2436",
  "title": "Hierarchical Facet Refinements level is always 0",
  "body": "**What is the current behavior?**\r\nI'm using `hierarchicalMenu` widget with attributes `['categories_en.lvl0', 'categories_en.lvl1', 'categories_en.lvl2', 'categories_en.lvl3']`.\r\n\r\nWhen I chose a category of level 2, it seems the refinement value is set with key `categories_en.lvl0` instead of `categories_en.lvl2`.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"603\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-10-03 at 12 35 34\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2593287/31123383-97da2504-a837-11e7-95a6-918dd5cb18f7.png\">\r\n\r\nThis means that the level 2 category is actually considered level 0.\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nI would expect the refinement to be `categories_en.lvl2`, thus allowing us to still refine `categories_en.lvl1` or `categories.lvl0`. Particularly, locking them down via `searchFunction` on initialisation on the page for a specific category.\r\n\r\n**What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nAll browsers. Using version instantsearch.js 2.1.6 currently.\r\n\r\n**What is the proposed solution?**\r\nEnsure refinement level matches that of what is selected.",
